<<<<<<<<<<<  Numeric Data Types  >>>>>>>>>>>


1.	Research and List: List and describe the different numeric data types available in MySQL. Provide examples for each.

    1-Integer Types


1-1 . TINYINT

Description: A very small integer.
Range:
Signed: -128 to 127
Unsigned: 0 to 255

1-2 . SMALLINT

Description: A small integer.
Range:
Signed: -32,768 to 32,767
Unsigned: 0 to 65,535

1-3 . MEDIUMINT

Description: A medium-sized integer.
Range:
Signed: -8,388,608 to 8,388,607
Unsigned: 0 to 16,777,215

1-4 . INT (or INTEGER)

Description: A standard integer.
Range:
Signed: -2,147,483,648 to 2,147,483,647
Unsigned: 0 to 4,294,967,295

1-5 . BIGINT

Description: A large integer.
Range:
Signed: -9,223,372,036,854,775,808 to 9,223,372,036,854,775,807
Unsigned: 0 to 18,446,744,073,709,551,615

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

    2-Fixed-Point Types

2-1 . DECIMAL (or NUMERIC)
Description: A fixed-point number.
Range: Defined by the user with precision and scale.

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

    3-Floating-Point Types

3-1 . FLOAT
Description: A small floating-point number.
Range: Approximate, based on precision.

3-2 . DOUBLE (or DOUBLE PRECISION)
Description: A double-precision floating-point number.
Range: Approximate, based on precision.

3-3 . REAL
Description: A synonym for DOUBLE.
Range: Same as DOUBLE.


